34
00:03:56,380 --> 00:03:57,690
你怎么能这样
How could you?

35
00:03:57,820 --> 00:04:00,120
-你怎么能不提前告诉我  -为了保护你
- How could you not warn me? - To protect you.

36
00:04:00,120 --> 00:04:02,690
-我是要保护你  -你别碰我
- I was protecting you. - You should take your hands off me.

37
00:04:02,700 --> 00:04:04,650
如果你觉得措手不及  我理解
No, look, I understand if you feel broadsided.

38
00:04:04,650 --> 00:04:06,240
-我不在意什么感觉  弗兰西斯  -但听我说
- I don't care about feelings, Francis. - But listen to me...

39
00:04:06,240 --> 00:04:07,320
克莱尔  听我说
Look, Claire, listen to me.

40
00:04:07,320 --> 00:04:09,200
你让我把丑出尽了
You made me look absolutely ridiculous.

41
00:04:09,200 --> 00:04:11,630
-毫无准备  稀里糊涂  -不  克莱尔
- Ill-prepared and ignorant. - No! Claire.

42
00:04:11,630 --> 00:04:13,060
-我们有一条规则  弗兰西斯  -不
- We have one rule, Francis. - No,

43
00:04:13,060 --> 00:04:14,760
-一条  -现在没了
- One rule.  - not anymore. Not anymore.

44
00:04:14,760 --> 00:04:16,800
-没了  -如果我不知道你的想法
- We don't. - I cannot be your ally

45
00:04:16,800 --> 00:04:18,330
就无法当你的盟友
if I don't know what you're thinking.

46
00:04:18,340 --> 00:04:20,870
克莱尔  事情本会闹个没完
Listen, Claire. It would have never ended.

47
00:04:20,870 --> 00:04:23,380
好吧  就算阻止了司法委员会
All right, fine, we got to stop judiciary,

48
00:04:23,380 --> 00:04:25,560
其他委员会也会冒出来
but other committees would have sprung up,

49
00:04:25,560 --> 00:04:27,170
一直指控我们
just to keep the charges going.

50
00:04:27,170 --> 00:04:30,800
监管  军事  外事  情报等等委员会
Oversight, Armed Services, Foreign Affairs, Intelligence.

51
00:04:30,800 --> 00:04:31,890
事情会没完没了的
It would have gone on and on.

52
00:04:31,890 --> 00:04:33,190
-年复一年的  -我不管  弗兰西斯
- Years and - I don't care, Francis.

53
00:04:33,190 --> 00:04:35,050
-调查  -你该跟我说的
- years of investigation. - You should have talked to me,

54
00:04:35,140 --> 00:04:37,490
而不是像这样临时决定
instead of making a last-minute decision like this.

55
00:04:37,490 --> 00:04:38,670
我没有
I didn't.

56
00:04:40,340 --> 00:04:46,180
我制造了这混乱  好利用它
I created this confusion in order to take advantage of it.

57
00:04:46,590 --> 00:04:51,570
所有事情都是计划好的
Everything that has happened... was planned.

58
00:04:53,780 --> 00:04:55,330
何时开始的
Since when?

59
00:04:55,570 --> 00:04:57,870
去极乐之地前
Since before Elysian Fields.

60
00:04:58,530 --> 00:05:01,290
但我是在极乐之地猛然领悟到
But it was at Elysian Fields that it hit me.

61
00:05:01,290 --> 00:05:02,560
我明白了
I saw it...

62
00:05:03,790 --> 00:05:07,280
就像头顶上的灯泡亮了起来
almost like a light bulb going off above my head.

63
00:05:08,570 --> 00:05:11,630
真正的权力在何处
Where does the real power lie?

64
00:05:11,920 --> 00:05:15,480
就是权力背后的权力
The power behind the power.

65
00:05:16,060 --> 00:05:17,760
克莱尔  我明白了
And I understood, Claire,

66
00:05:17,760 --> 00:05:22,410
我们不能像过去那样思考行动
that we have to think and act differently than we ever have.

67
00:05:22,410 --> 00:05:26,210
因为关键已经不在于谁住在白宫
Because it's no longer about who lives in the White House...

68
00:05:28,590 --> 00:05:31,410
而在于谁拥有白宫
it's about who owns the White House.

69
00:05:31,730 --> 00:05:35,180
这可是总统一职  政客还能爬多高
This is the presidency. How much higher can a politician go?

70
00:05:35,190 --> 00:05:37,800
真正的权力不在这儿
The real power isn't here.

71
00:05:38,900 --> 00:05:40,610
而在之外
It's beyond here.

72
00:05:40,610 --> 00:05:43,850
超越了它  但仍要与之配合工作
It's above it, but still working in conjunction with it.

73
00:05:43,850 --> 00:05:46,830
克莱尔  你我一直都在圈内
Look, Claire, you and I have always been on the inside.

74
00:05:46,830 --> 00:05:49,510
被困在泡泡里
Trapped. In the bubble.

75
00:05:51,090 --> 00:05:52,590
但从今往后
But going forward...

76
00:05:53,460 --> 00:05:57,200
我在私营部门经营圈外
with my operating on the outside, in the private sector,

77
00:05:57,200 --> 00:06:00,620
你在这里工作
and you working from here...

78
00:06:02,560 --> 00:06:05,940
我们能一起拥有白宫
we can own this house together.

79
00:06:08,400 --> 00:06:12,720
你不明白吗  这是我计划好的
Don't you see? I've designed this.

80
00:06:13,620 --> 00:06:16,600
我想让你当总统
I wanted you to be the president.

81
00:06:16,870 --> 00:06:20,610
我让你成为了总统
I've made you the president.

82
00:06:23,690 --> 00:06:25,860
我该向你道谢吗
Am I supposed to say thank you?

83
00:06:26,290 --> 00:06:27,220
不
No.

84
00:06:28,170 --> 00:06:32,210
但你得赦免我  赦免我所有的罪行
But you will have to pardon me. Pardon me for all of my crimes.

85
00:06:32,220 --> 00:06:34,300
作为总统  只有你才能这么做
As the president, you're the only one who can.

86
00:06:34,300 --> 00:06:35,680
弗兰西斯  如果我这么做会被弹劾
Francis, I could be impeached if I do that.

87
00:06:35,680 --> 00:06:37,630
不会的  戴维斯和厄舍
No, no. Look, Davis and Usher,

88
00:06:37,630 --> 00:06:39,730
他们可以保护你
they're in a position to protect you.

89
00:06:39,730 --> 00:06:43,090
-他们希望你成功  -世事难料  弗兰西斯
- They want you to succeed. - We can be sure of nothing, Francis.

90
00:06:43,090 --> 00:06:44,520
道格的事
Everything going on with Doug,

91
00:06:44,520 --> 00:06:45,530
白宫还有泄密者
the leak still in the White House...

92
00:06:45,530 --> 00:06:47,220
不  那也是我
No, that was me, too.

93
00:06:49,470 --> 00:06:51,510
-什么  -我就是泄密者
- What? - I'm the leak.

94
00:06:52,390 --> 00:06:54,390
这几个月我一直在道格的帮助下
I've been feeding information to Tom Hammerschmidt

95
00:06:54,390 --> 00:06:56,500
给汤姆·汉默施密特放料
for months with Doug's help.

96
00:06:58,080 --> 00:07:00,390
这没道理  弗兰西斯
That doesn't make any sense, Francis.

97
00:07:00,390 --> 00:07:03,450
克莱尔  如果你在别人之前扳倒自己
Claire, when you bring yourself down before someone else can,

98
00:07:03,460 --> 00:07:05,780
你就能控制这个过程了
you control the way it happens.

99
00:07:06,730 --> 00:07:11,730
只有这条路才能让我们来到此刻
This was the only path to get us to this moment

100
00:07:11,800 --> 00:07:15,980
你和我  能够拥有一切
where you and I can own it all.

101
00:07:24,660 --> 00:07:26,450
撤掉监控
Get rid of the surveillance.

102
00:07:27,140 --> 00:07:30,930
抹除一切  停掉一切  你跟道格做的一切
Erase it. Shut everything down. Anything you and Doug were up to.

103
00:07:31,240 --> 00:07:34,590
好  但是你得先赦免我
All right. But you have to pardon me first.

104
00:07:34,590 --> 00:07:36,940
等时机合适  还要赦免道格
And, at the right time, Doug.

105
00:07:37,110 --> 00:07:39,200
否则我们可能都要进监狱
Or we could both go to prison.

106
00:07:42,250 --> 00:07:43,640
我杀了汤姆
I killed Tom.

107
00:07:44,120 --> 00:07:46,770
我杀了汤姆·耶茨  他死了
I killed Tom Yates. He's dead.

108
00:07:48,110 --> 00:07:50,200
我让马克处理掉了
And I had Mark clean it up.

109
00:07:51,490 --> 00:07:54,430
所以这永远不会追查到我们
So it will never make its way back to us.

110
00:08:00,320 --> 00:08:02,930
那我们都做了必须做的事
Well, then I guess we both did what we had to.

111
00:08:05,300 --> 00:08:06,730
-你知道他要做这事吗  -不知道
- Did you know he was gonna do this? - No.

112
00:08:06,730 --> 00:08:11,540
因为这很不好  克莱尔  这非常不好
Because this is bad, Claire. This is very... very bad.

113
00:08:13,510 --> 00:08:14,780
天哪
My God!

114
00:08:16,080 --> 00:08:17,520
你们两个怎么回事
What is it with you two?

115
00:08:17,760 --> 00:08:20,530
-如果你在想什么  说...  -在我家里
- If there's something on your mind, say... - In my house?

116
00:08:21,060 --> 00:08:22,280
你把他留在我家里了
You left him in my house?!

117
00:08:22,280 --> 00:08:25,600
小声点  至少改变你的语气
Lower your voice, or at least change your tone.

118
00:08:26,330 --> 00:08:27,800
你处理好了吗
Did you take care of it?

119
00:08:30,680 --> 00:08:32,080
是的  那是我的工作
Yes, that's what I do.

120
00:08:32,330 --> 00:08:34,360
那谢谢你  做得好
Then thank you, and well done.

121
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:36,590
现在我们回到眼前的事
Now let's get back to what's in front of us.

122
00:08:36,590 --> 00:08:38,040
他想让你待在这里吗  克莱尔
Does he even want you to be here, Claire?

123
00:08:38,040 --> 00:08:41,130
马克  拜托  我现在需要的是你的政治盘算
Mark, please. What I need right now is your political calculus.

124
00:08:41,130 --> 00:08:45,210
他将你和我们所有人置于了为难的境地
He has put you, he has put all of us, in an impossible position.

125
00:08:45,210 --> 00:08:46,060
你明白吗
You see that?

126
00:08:47,930 --> 00:08:51,260
如果你不能正确处理这件事  就无法恢复了
If you don't handle this correctly, you do not recover from it.

127
00:08:51,260 --> 00:08:54,360
这事关政府的持续运作
This is about continuity of government.

128
00:08:55,180 --> 00:08:57,470
通知北约  通知各国领导人
Informing NATO, informing world leaders.

129
00:08:57,470 --> 00:08:59,850
我们本该让大使们待命的
We should have had ambassadors on call.

130
00:08:59,850 --> 00:09:01,870
参谋长联席会议  国家安全...
Joint Chiefs of Staff, the National Security...

131
00:09:01,870 --> 00:09:04,580
连尼克松都那样做了
Even Nixon did that!

132
00:09:08,730 --> 00:09:10,270
我准备好上交了
I'm ready to hand it over,

133
00:09:10,280 --> 00:09:11,920
但是我要得到保证  不管怎样
but I want to be assured that no matter what,

134
00:09:11,920 --> 00:09:14,010
麦卡伦之死不会牵连到我
Macallan's death is not related to me.

135
00:09:14,010 --> 00:09:15,690
这可以办到
That can be taken care of.

136
00:09:16,270 --> 00:09:18,950
-我要你手上我的东西  -好
- I want what you have of mine. - Okay.

137
00:09:18,990 --> 00:09:20,380
会给你的
That's what you'll get.

138
00:09:20,440 --> 00:09:22,660
我还要当幕僚长
And I want to be Chief of Staff.

139
00:09:25,230 --> 00:09:27,100
我觉得这不是问题
Well, I don't think that's a problem.

140
00:09:28,270 --> 00:09:30,350
很高兴你在提要求
I'm glad you're asking for what you want.

141
00:09:37,060 --> 00:09:39,410
道格·斯坦普会为总统做任何事
Doug Stamper would do anything for the president.

142
00:09:39,410 --> 00:09:40,850
他看到了佐伊·巴恩斯的威胁
He saw a threat in Zoe Barnes,

143
00:09:40,850 --> 00:09:42,860
她跟总统有私情
who the president was involved with.

144
00:09:43,560 --> 00:09:44,820
他就处理掉了
And he took care of it.

145
00:09:45,320 --> 00:09:47,700
他不止一次地威胁过我的生命
He's threatened my life on numerous occasions.

146
00:09:48,390 --> 00:09:51,140
-但是回到我的问题  -不  女士
- But to go back to my question... - No, ma'am.

147
00:09:51,140 --> 00:09:54,040
我不认为总统知道道格在做什么
I don't think the president knew what Doug was up to.

148
00:09:54,430 --> 00:09:55,490
完全不了解
Not at all.

149
00:10:02,600 --> 00:10:03,890
汉默施密特先生
Mr. Hammerschmidt.

150
00:10:04,860 --> 00:10:06,350
我想给你打电话来着
I've been meaning to call you.

151
00:10:09,930 --> 00:10:10,960
肖恩
Sean.

152
00:10:12,040 --> 00:10:13,640
你应该能看出来  我现在在这里工作
As you can tell, I work here now.

153
00:10:15,550 --> 00:10:17,590
我现在跟你握手
I'm shaking your hand right now

154
00:10:17,590 --> 00:10:20,280
是因为我崇尚社交礼仪
because I believe in social graces.

155
00:10:22,390 --> 00:10:23,820
你迷失了
You're lost.

156
00:10:24,660 --> 00:10:27,370
-我不这么认为  -不  你就是迷失了
- I don't think so. - No, you are.

157
00:10:27,740 --> 00:10:29,580
不  我一点都没迷失
No, not at all.

158
00:10:29,630 --> 00:10:31,120
这就是你想要的
This is what you wanted?

159
00:10:31,680 --> 00:10:36,070
为腐败的政府和走向毁灭的总统卖命
A job in a corrupt administration? Presidency in ruin?

160
00:10:36,230 --> 00:10:37,640
我是在白宫里面
I'm in the White House.

161
00:10:37,640 --> 00:10:40,050
不是在外面  好奇着里面是什么样
Not out there, wondering what it's like in here.

162
00:10:41,410 --> 00:10:42,490
不会很久的
Not for long.

163
00:10:44,010 --> 00:10:47,560
你一旦进来了  就是进来了  这就是美国特色
Once you're in, you're in. It's the American way.

164
00:10:47,760 --> 00:10:50,450
-斯坦普先生现在可以见你了  -谢谢
- Mr. Stamper will see you now. - Thank you.

165
00:10:58,070 --> 00:10:59,620
抱歉让你久等了
Sorry to keep you waiting.

166
00:10:59,900 --> 00:11:01,250
当我提出这次会面时  我不知道
When I asked for this meeting, I had no idea

167
00:11:01,250 --> 00:11:04,020
总统今晚要签字辞职
the president would be signing his resignation this evening.

168
00:11:05,270 --> 00:11:06,750
还有我  今天早上辞职
And I, this morning.

169
00:11:08,080 --> 00:11:10,670
-我听说了传闻  -现在确定了
- I heard a rumor you might. - Now it's confirmed.

170
00:11:10,880 --> 00:11:12,210
斯坦普先生
Mr. Stamper...

171
00:11:12,280 --> 00:11:14,790
请说  你可以叫我道格
Yeah, please. You can call me Doug.

172
00:11:15,420 --> 00:11:18,360
还是免了  毕竟这是正式采访
I'd rather not, for the sake of this interview.

173
00:11:18,940 --> 00:11:21,100
希望你知道这不是私下谈话
I want you to know this will not be off the record,

174
00:11:21,100 --> 00:11:22,390
或作为幕后消息
or on background.

175
00:11:25,150 --> 00:11:29,000
我确实认识丽萨·威廉姆斯  几年前认识的
I do know Lisa Williams. I met her a couple years ago.

176
00:11:31,780 --> 00:11:32,720
好的
Okay.

177
00:11:33,770 --> 00:11:35,690
但在我们谈其他事之前
But before we get to anything else...

178
00:11:38,360 --> 00:11:39,540
安德伍德总统
did President Underwood,

179
00:11:39,540 --> 00:11:42,140
在还是议员时  是否杀害了佐伊·巴恩斯
when he was congressman, kill Zoe Barnes?

180
00:11:45,370 --> 00:11:46,270
没有
No.

181
00:11:47,660 --> 00:11:49,060
斯坦普先生
Mr. Stamper...

182
00:11:52,540 --> 00:11:54,520
你是否杀害了佐伊·巴恩斯
did you kill Zoe Barnes?

183
00:11:54,890 --> 00:11:56,850
我没准备好回答那个问题
I'm not prepared to answer that question.

184
00:11:58,030 --> 00:12:01,030
你明白我可以白纸黑字写明你拒绝回答吧
You understand I can use your refusal in print.

185
00:12:01,790 --> 00:12:02,700
明白
Yes.

186
00:12:03,550 --> 00:12:06,130
佐伊死的那天  你是否在大教堂高地
Were you on the Cathedral Heights D.C. Metro platform

187
00:12:06,130 --> 00:12:07,630
地铁站的站台上
the day of Zoe's death?

188
00:12:07,660 --> 00:12:09,680
任何涉及佐伊·巴恩斯的问题
Any questions regarding Zoe Barnes,

189
00:12:09,680 --> 00:12:11,530
你得去跟我的律师谈
you need to speak with my attorneys.

190
00:12:16,130 --> 00:12:18,930
佐伊·巴恩斯是否用一部一次性手机
Did Zoe Barnes make a call to Francis Underwood

191
00:12:18,940 --> 00:12:21,810
打给了时任议员的弗兰西斯·安德伍德
from a burner phone when he was congressman?

192
00:12:22,380 --> 00:12:25,250
-你为什么要问我  -你为什么不回答
- Why would you ask me that? - Why won't you answer?

193
00:12:25,250 --> 00:12:27,590
总统的手机几乎都是我在接
I almost always answer the president's phone.

194
00:12:27,590 --> 00:12:29,430
电话  短信
Calls, texts...

195
00:12:31,730 --> 00:12:33,600
你知道那些短信吗
Do you have any knowledge of those texts?

196
00:12:33,750 --> 00:12:35,620
我没准备好作出评论
I'm not prepared to comment on that.

197
00:12:36,420 --> 00:12:38,470
那么这次谈话到此为止
Then this conversation is over.

198
00:12:44,780 --> 00:12:45,980
祝好
Have a good day.

199
00:12:50,970 --> 00:12:52,170
最后一件事
One last thing.

200
00:12:53,220 --> 00:12:55,120
你是否给我寄过两张生日贺卡
Did you send me two birthday cards?

201
00:12:55,800 --> 00:12:56,710
没有
No.

202
00:13:03,660 --> 00:13:05,050
[苏格兰盖尔语]
Slàinte mhath.

203
00:13:05,410 --> 00:13:07,680
是苏格兰盖尔语  意思是"祝安康"
That's Scottish Gaelic. It means "Good health."

204
00:13:07,680 --> 00:13:09,580
我父亲有点执迷
My father's kind of obsessed.

205
00:13:09,580 --> 00:13:11,220
他将我们格雷森家的历史
And he traced our line of Graysons back to,

206
00:13:11,220 --> 00:13:13,640
追溯到了16世纪左右
like, 16th century or something.

207
00:13:13,940 --> 00:13:16,770
如果我们午休时需要喝一杯
Well, if we ever needed a drink in the middle of the day...

208
00:13:17,940 --> 00:13:20,850
联邦检察官那边进展顺利
It went well with the US attorney.

209
00:13:22,630 --> 00:13:24,000
真令人悲痛
It's tragic.

210
00:13:24,690 --> 00:13:28,210
一想到道格做了什么  我们的心都碎了
Our hearts are just broken at the thought of what Doug did.

211
00:13:29,150 --> 00:13:30,740
我不知道他怎么了
I don't know what happened to him.

212
00:13:31,470 --> 00:13:33,600
可能到了某个时候...
I guess somewhere along the line...

213
00:13:35,060 --> 00:13:37,260
他什么时候会宣布辞职
When will, uh, he be announcing his resignation?

214
00:13:37,260 --> 00:13:40,130
-今天下午  -当然
- It's happening this afternoon. - Oh, of course.

215
00:13:40,130 --> 00:13:43,220
赛斯  你也得辞职
And, Seth, you'll need to resign as well.

216
00:13:47,090 --> 00:13:49,710
-我还以为  -我知道  但你想想
- I thought that, uh... - I know, but think about this.

217
00:13:49,750 --> 00:13:53,360
我得建立我自己的团队  得公开进行
I need to establish my own team. Publicly.

218
00:13:53,370 --> 00:13:54,800
不能回避
And there's no avoiding

219
00:13:54,810 --> 00:13:57,690
目前你跟道格和弗兰西斯的关系有多紧密
how tied you and Doug are to Francis at this point.

220
00:13:57,690 --> 00:14:02,270
这只是为了等一切烟消云散  仅此而已
So, it's really just waiting for the dust to settle. That's all.

221
00:14:02,960 --> 00:14:04,390
怎么感觉像是你在告诉我
Why does it feel like you're telling me

222
00:14:04,400 --> 00:14:06,200
我的职业生涯结束了  副总统女士
my career is over, Madam Vice President?

223
00:14:06,210 --> 00:14:10,280
不  我只是说  你得先离开一阵子
No, I'm just saying, you just need to go away for a little while.

224
00:14:10,770 --> 00:14:12,780
稍后我们会召你回来的
And we'll bring you back into the fold at a later date,

225
00:14:12,780 --> 00:14:14,070
不用担心
and don't worry.

226
00:14:14,610 --> 00:14:17,600
看看莉安  她也离开过  现在她回来了
Look at LeAnn. She left and now she's back.

227
00:14:19,910 --> 00:14:21,880
我们以前一起喝过酒吗
Have we ever had a drink together?

228
00:14:23,740 --> 00:14:24,670
从来没有
Never.

229
00:14:43,180 --> 00:14:45,410
我想在您还是总统时  把这个交给您
I wanted to hand this to you while you were still president.

230
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:57,290
我带着沉重的心情接受了
I accept this with a heavy heart.

231
00:15:00,430 --> 00:15:02,960
我昨天跟律师们开了一个战略会议
I had a strategy session with the attorneys yesterday.

232
00:15:03,630 --> 00:15:05,690
希望他们好好对你了
I hope they're treating you well.

233
00:15:08,970 --> 00:15:09,910
你知道
You know...

234
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:13,970
道格  现在起
Doug, we're not gonna be able

235
00:15:13,970 --> 00:15:16,530
我们将有一阵子不能见面了
to see each other for some time now.

236
00:15:24,250 --> 00:15:26,310
不如你拿点什么东西当纪念吧
So why don't you take something?

237
00:15:27,090 --> 00:15:29,150
-不了  -没关系  随意挑吧
- No. - No, no. Go on. Take something.

238
00:15:29,160 --> 00:15:32,400
任何东西  你想要什么都行  即便很小
Anything. Anything you want. Even if it's small.

239
00:15:33,470 --> 00:15:35,880
一个你能握在手里
Something you can hold in your hand

240
00:15:36,270 --> 00:15:41,270
让你回想起这里的东西  直到你回来
to remind you of this place... until you get back.

241
00:15:42,730 --> 00:15:43,760
随便选吧
You go on.

242
00:16:50,290 --> 00:16:53,870
离我的正式辞职只有几小时了
We're a few hours away from my official resignation...

243
00:16:54,330 --> 00:16:58,350
而你还没答应赦免我
and you still have not agreed to pardon me.

244
00:16:59,420 --> 00:17:00,740
如果你不
And if you don't,

245
00:17:01,050 --> 00:17:04,760
我将不得不撤回辞职的决定
I will be forced to renege on that resignation.

246
00:17:05,260 --> 00:17:07,130
那就太过分了
That would be outrageous.

247
00:17:07,130 --> 00:17:11,380
我递交了签字辞呈  才算正式辞职
Well, it isn't official until I submit a signed letter.

248
00:17:12,200 --> 00:17:14,400
这对你余下的总统任期有什么好处
And what would that do to the rest of your presidency?

249
00:17:14,400 --> 00:17:16,170
还能剩下什么
What would be left of it?

250
00:17:16,170 --> 00:17:17,110
克莱尔  如果你不同意
Claire, if you don't do it,

251
00:17:17,110 --> 00:17:19,450
你可能就要与重罪犯是夫妻了
you're gonna risk being married to a felon.

252
00:17:19,500 --> 00:17:22,000
如果我同意  那又置我于何地
And if I do, where does that leave me?

253
00:17:22,010 --> 00:17:24,970
你现在真的想和我谈这个吗
Look, is this really the conversation you want to be having?

254
00:17:24,970 --> 00:17:26,260
你给我设局  弗兰西斯
You've trapped me, Francis.

255
00:17:26,260 --> 00:17:29,330
不  我不接受害了你的指责
No, I do not accept that I've done something to you.

256
00:17:29,450 --> 00:17:33,290
我给你提供了一个机会
I have provided you with an opportunity.

257
00:17:33,290 --> 00:17:37,650
你之前也说过  这就是你的终局
Now, you have said before, that this is your endgame.

258
00:17:37,650 --> 00:17:41,920
眼下你的终极目标唾手可得
And now, your goal is within spitting distance

259
00:17:41,920 --> 00:17:45,880
而你只看到了背叛  我不信
and all you see is betrayal? I don't buy it.

260
00:17:48,480 --> 00:17:51,210
别再纠结我对你做了什么了
Stop talking about what I've done to you.

261
00:17:54,850 --> 00:17:55,950
承认吧
Admit it.

262
00:17:57,250 --> 00:17:59,420
这就是你想要的
This is what you want.

263
00:17:59,970 --> 00:18:02,110
你愿意为之杀人
You were willing to kill for it.

264
00:18:03,590 --> 00:18:05,600
那么克莱尔  接受吧
So, Claire, come and take it...

265
00:18:07,420 --> 00:18:09,510
不然我就要收回了
before I take it back.

266
00:18:17,480 --> 00:18:21,200
我们要挑选最合适的时机和地点
We'll find the most strategic time and place.

267
00:18:21,400 --> 00:18:23,670
但我会特赦你  弗兰西斯
But I will pardon you, Francis.

268
00:18:26,920 --> 00:18:31,840
{\an7}{\pos(92.4,130.05)}尊敬的国务卿女士
我谨辞去合众国总统职务
此致  弗兰西斯·J·安德伍德

269
00:18:51,230 --> 00:18:53,650
为了国家利益  我们也应该解散委员会
For the good of the nation, we need to disband this committee,

270
00:18:52,200 --> 00:19:02,200
{\an1}{\pos(123,229.05)}罗梅洛议员呼吁在总统辞职后解散司法委员会

271
00:18:53,650 --> 00:18:55,340
把这一页翻过去
and put this behind us.

272
00:18:55,440 --> 00:18:58,510
总统很可能撑不过听证会
The president most likely would not have survived the hearings.

273
00:18:58,510 --> 00:19:01,710
你也可以说他是被迫辞职
You could argue that he had no choice but to resign.

274
00:19:02,170 --> 00:19:04,740
但我们也不能否认他的证词引起很大反响
But we can't deny that his testimony struck a chord.

275
00:19:04,740 --> 00:19:06,320
就算是这样
Well, that may be true.

276
00:19:06,320 --> 00:19:09,120
那你  罗梅洛议员
But how is it that you, Congressman Romero,

277
00:19:09,120 --> 00:19:12,940
他最主要的批评者  怎么转而支持他了呢
his biggest critic, are supporting him now?

278
00:19:15,360 --> 00:19:16,380
历史
History.

279
00:19:16,920 --> 00:19:17,870
今天结束时
By the end of the day,

280
00:19:17,870 --> 00:19:20,530
我们国家会第一次有位女总统
the country will have its first woman president.

281
00:19:21,110 --> 00:19:23,040
我一直支持有一位女性
Look, I've always been a supporter of the idea

282
00:19:23,040 --> 00:19:24,420
能入主白宫
of a woman in the Oval Office.

283
00:19:24,420 --> 00:19:27,270
但是说到底
But when all is said and done,

284
00:19:27,270 --> 00:19:30,210
您应该清楚弗兰西斯·安德伍德
you do realize that Francis Underwood

285
00:19:30,220 --> 00:19:33,170
今晚还是会在白宫过夜的吧
will still be sleeping in the White House tonight?

286
00:19:46,860 --> 00:19:48,580
你不是该收拾东西了吗
Isn't this when you pack everything up?

287
00:19:48,730 --> 00:19:50,540
至少带走个人物品
Or at least take the personal things?

288
00:19:50,970 --> 00:19:52,640
我什么都不拿了
I'm not taking anything.

289
00:19:55,230 --> 00:19:56,800
任你处置吧
You can do what you want with it.

290
00:20:02,600 --> 00:20:05,570
-你什么时候见联邦检察官  -后天
- When do you meet with the US attorney? - Day after tomorrow.

291
00:20:12,220 --> 00:20:15,390
我从没想过弗兰克·安德伍德会下台
I never thought that Frank Underwood would not be president.

292
00:20:16,280 --> 00:20:17,320
真没想过
Not really.

293
00:20:22,040 --> 00:20:23,880
你可以逃跑
You could just run away.

294
00:20:25,470 --> 00:20:26,780
那我有什么好处
What does that get me?

295
00:20:27,540 --> 00:20:29,650
你很擅长照顾自己
You're good at taking care of yourself.

296
00:20:31,280 --> 00:20:32,320
真好笑
That's funny.

297
00:20:33,570 --> 00:20:35,740
我希望你知道我关心你
Look, I want you to know that I care for you,

298
00:20:35,740 --> 00:20:38,660
但恐怕我也帮不上你什么了
but I don't know how much I can be there.

299
00:20:45,400 --> 00:20:47,370
我想就在这里坐一会儿
I think I'm gonna just sit here for a while.

300
00:20:48,580 --> 00:20:49,940
嗯  坐吧
Yeah, you should.

301
00:20:55,970 --> 00:20:58,330
副总统希望你在她宣誓就职之前
Uh, the vice president would like you to leave the White House

302
00:20:58,330 --> 00:21:00,080
离开白宫
before she's sworn in.

303
00:21:02,870 --> 00:21:05,350
她认为最好不要传出什么她就职时
She doesn't think it would be a good idea for word to get out

304
00:21:05,350 --> 00:21:07,080
你还在白宫的消息
that you were here when it happened.

305
00:21:34,340 --> 00:21:37,530
本人庄严宣誓  我必忠实执行
I do solemnly swear that I will faithfully execute

306
00:21:37,530 --> 00:21:40,980
合众国总统职务
the office of President of the United States,

307
00:21:41,020 --> 00:21:45,000
忠于职守  竭尽全力  恪守  维护
and will to the best of my ability preserve, protect

308
00:21:45,010 --> 00:21:48,510
和捍卫合众国宪法
and defend the Constitution of the United States.

309
00:21:48,640 --> 00:21:50,870
-愿上帝助我  -又是这熟悉的一幕
- So help me God. - Here we are again.

310
00:21:50,920 --> 00:21:53,180
知道吗  如果你忽略盛大的仪式和场合
You know, if you ignore all the pomp and circumstance,

311
00:21:53,180 --> 00:21:57,500
最反常的事就是我真的相信总统之位
the most perverse thing is I actually believe in the presidency.

312
00:21:57,500 --> 00:21:58,540
其重要性
Its importance.

313
00:21:58,540 --> 00:22:01,370
对世界的重大意义  哪怕只是象征性的
What it means around the world, even symbolically.

314
00:22:01,370 --> 00:22:06,370
但我更相信权力  信它本身
But I believe in power even more. For its own sake.

315
00:22:07,040 --> 00:22:08,730
戈尔·维达尔[作家]曾写道
Gore Vidal once wrote

316
00:22:08,770 --> 00:22:11,380
权力的目的是权力
that power is an end to itself,

317
00:22:11,380 --> 00:22:15,550
而夺取胜利的本能冲动
and the instinctive urge to prevail...

318
00:22:15,880 --> 00:22:18,880
是人类最为重要的特性
the most important single human trait.

319
00:22:19,920 --> 00:22:23,400
我总是告诉我自己  我做的一切都是为了她
I've always told myself that everything I did was for her.

320
00:22:23,400 --> 00:22:28,320
但也许并不是  也许我更爱权力
But maybe it wasn't. Maybe I love power more.

321
00:22:29,320 --> 00:22:32,470
为你  和你亲爱的人
For you, and for any dear to you,

322
00:22:32,580 --> 00:22:34,300
我愿做任何事
I would do anything.

323
00:22:34,760 --> 00:22:37,310
如果有幸  我的生涯中
If my career were of that better kind

324
00:22:37,310 --> 00:22:42,150
有做出牺牲的机会或是能力
that there was any opportunity or capacity to sacrifice in it,

325
00:22:42,160 --> 00:22:47,160
我愿抓住一切机会  为你和你亲爱的人牺牲
I would embrace any sacrifice for you and for those dear to you.

326
00:22:47,700 --> 00:22:52,060
在宁静的时候  请记得我
Try to hold me in your mind, at some quiet times,

327
00:22:52,060 --> 00:22:55,560
记得我这番热情而真挚的话
as ardent and sincere in this one thing.

328
00:22:56,190 --> 00:22:57,710
那一天终会到来
The time will come,

329
00:22:57,830 --> 00:22:59,870
那一天已经不远
the time will not be long in coming,

330
00:22:59,870 --> 00:23:02,800
你将建立起新的关系
when new ties will be formed about you.

331
00:23:02,900 --> 00:23:07,750
那关系将会更加温情而有力地把你
The ties that will bind you yet more tenderly and strongly

332
00:23:07,750 --> 00:23:10,420
跟你悉心经营的家连结在一起
to the home you so adorn.

333
00:23:11,010 --> 00:23:14,810
那是永远为你增光  令你幸福的最亲密的关系
The dearest ties that will ever grace and gladden you.

334
00:23:15,210 --> 00:23:16,580
马内特小姐
Oh, Miss Manette,

335
00:23:16,690 --> 00:23:18,000
等一个长得
when the little picture

336
00:23:18,000 --> 00:23:21,260
和他幸福的父亲一样的小家伙仰起脸看你时
of a happy father's face looks up in yours...

337
00:23:34,090 --> 00:23:35,140
晚上好
Good evening.

338
00:23:37,710 --> 00:23:40,310
晚上好  女士们先生们  我叫肖恩·杰弗瑞斯
Good evening, ladies and gentlemen. My name is Sean Jeffries.

339
00:23:40,310 --> 00:23:42,850
我是新新闻部副主任
I'm the new deputy director of communications.

340
00:23:42,850 --> 00:23:43,790
赛斯去哪了
Where's Seth?

341
00:23:43,790 --> 00:23:45,550
格雷森先生上台前被叫走了
Mr. Grayson got called away last minute,

342
00:23:45,550 --> 00:23:48,410
所以我临时替代一下他
so I'm temporarily filling his shoes.

343
00:23:49,890 --> 00:23:52,450
我不回答问题
I won't be taking any questions.

344
00:23:52,450 --> 00:23:55,560
我要读一份拟好的声明
Instead, I'll be reading from a prepared statement.

345
00:23:56,650 --> 00:23:58,030
几小时前
A few hours ago,

346
00:23:58,030 --> 00:23:59,350
安德伍德总统
President Underwood resigned

347
00:23:59,350 --> 00:24:01,780
辞去了美国总统一职
the office of President of the United States.

348
00:24:01,780 --> 00:24:04,390
在有白宫人员参加的私密仪式上
And in a private ceremony attended by staff,

349
00:24:04,390 --> 00:24:07,220
克莱尔·安德伍德总统宣誓就职
President Claire Underwood was sworn in.

350
00:24:07,430 --> 00:24:09,970
即刻生效  她将担任
Effective immediately, she will be assuming the office

351
00:24:09,970 --> 00:24:12,580
美国总统一职
of President of the United States.

352
00:24:12,810 --> 00:24:14,460
稍后会具体公布将由
Details will be coming shortly on who will

353
00:24:14,460 --> 00:24:15,760
-谁来接任  -你一定很为他骄傲
- be stepping into the office as - You must be so proud of him.

354
00:24:15,760 --> 00:24:16,390
副总统
vice president.

355
00:24:16,760 --> 00:24:19,270
弗兰西斯·安德伍德总统今天虽无法亲自前来
And while President Francis Underwood couldn't be here today...

356
00:24:19,270 --> 00:24:21,740
三小时前进行了权力交接
Transfer of power happened three hours ago,

357
00:24:21,740 --> 00:24:24,640
过程"私密而低调"
quote, "privately and quietly."

358
00:24:24,640 --> 00:24:26,080
头版头条就是它了
And that's above the fold.

359
00:24:26,080 --> 00:24:28,240
-司法部有什么消息吗  -还没有
- Anything from DOJ? - Nothing yet.

360
00:24:28,240 --> 00:24:29,390
马克·厄舍没有正式头衔
No official title to him,

361
00:24:29,390 --> 00:24:31,660
但权力交接是他主持的
but it's Mark Usher running the transition.

362
00:24:31,670 --> 00:24:35,680
好  我们来看看谁进谁出
Okay. Let's find out who's in and who's out.

363
00:24:35,680 --> 00:24:37,630
多米诺骨牌在不断倒下
The dominoes are falling.

364
00:24:37,750 --> 00:24:39,600
-谁负责调查罗梅洛  -我
- Now, who's on Romero? - Here.

365
00:24:40,070 --> 00:24:42,950
-我们想让议员公开发声  -好的
- We want the congressman on the record. - I've got it.

366
00:24:42,950 --> 00:24:45,350
留着麦卡伦周末再爆料
And let's save Macallan for the weekend.

367
00:24:45,620 --> 00:24:48,000
汤姆  道格·斯坦普怎么样了
Tom, where are we with Doug Stamper?

368
00:24:48,660 --> 00:24:50,570
我得去核查点东西
There's, uh, something I need to check on.

369
00:24:50,570 --> 00:24:51,820
头条网  消息网
Slugline, BuzzFeed,

370
00:24:51,820 --> 00:24:54,310
全市一半的新闻渠道都等着这则大新闻呢
half the outlets in this city are ready to jump on this.

371
00:24:54,310 --> 00:24:56,280
你跟他一对一谈过
You spoke to him. One on one.

372
00:24:56,280 --> 00:24:59,390
-他没说是他干的  -他不用说
- He didn't actually say he did it. - He doesn't have to.

373
00:24:59,730 --> 00:25:03,350
有人知道赛斯·格雷森对联邦检察官说了什么吗
Does anyone know what Seth Grayson said to the US attorney?

374
00:25:05,850 --> 00:25:06,810
汤姆
Tom?

375
00:25:10,480 --> 00:25:13,180
你写这届政府写了两年了
Two years you've been writing about this administration.

376
00:25:13,180 --> 00:25:16,090
-机会来了  -我想继续追查而已
- This is it. - I want to follow up, that's all.

377
00:25:17,710 --> 00:25:19,950
我看见一座美丽的城市
I see a beautiful city

378
00:25:19,950 --> 00:25:23,340
和一个灿烂的民族从这深渊中升起
and a brilliant people rising from this abyss.

379
00:25:23,340 --> 00:25:26,300
在他们争取真正的自由的奋斗中
And in their struggles to be truly free,

380
00:25:26,670 --> 00:25:28,990
在他们的胜利与失败中
in their triumphs and defeats,

381
00:25:28,990 --> 00:25:31,090
在未来的漫长岁月中
through long years to come,

382
00:25:31,180 --> 00:25:35,150
我看见这一时代的邪恶和前一时代的邪恶
I see the evil of this time and of the previous time

383
00:25:35,150 --> 00:25:38,130
前者是后者的自然结果
of which this is the natural birth,

384
00:25:38,130 --> 00:25:43,130
逐渐赎去自己的罪孽  慢慢消失
gradually making expiation for itself and wearing out.

385
00:25:44,320 --> 00:25:46,720
华盛顿时间今天凌晨三点左右
Surface-to-surface missiles delivered sarin

386
00:25:46,720 --> 00:25:49,430
地对地沙林毒气导弹
at about three o'clock in the morning, our time.

387
00:25:49,430 --> 00:25:52,520
莫斯科已经发出声明  谴责反政府军
Moscow has already issued a statement condemning the rebels

388
00:25:52,520 --> 00:25:55,380
策划了这场苦肉计袭击
for orchestrating the attack on themselves.

389
00:25:55,380 --> 00:25:57,810
-真是吗  -当然不是
- And did they? - Of course not.

390
00:25:58,060 --> 00:26:01,010
佩特罗夫是想利用它发动正当空袭
Petrov will use this to justify air strikes.

391
00:26:01,720 --> 00:26:04,270
我给你看张照片
I'd like to show you an image.

392
00:26:11,280 --> 00:26:13,500
这张是路透社的
This one is coming out of Reuters.

393
00:26:13,960 --> 00:26:17,400
我有预感  上午大多数媒体都会发这张
The feeling is most of the press will be using it by the a.m.

394
00:26:18,140 --> 00:26:19,300
依我的经验
Experience tells me

395
00:26:19,300 --> 00:26:22,120
这件事会回响个三五天
this will resonate for about three to five days...

396
00:26:23,000 --> 00:26:24,610
也就给了我们机会
which gives us our window.

397
00:26:24,610 --> 00:26:26,240
我们可以准备一份声明
Well, we can ready a statement.

398
00:26:26,240 --> 00:26:28,730
出兵才是真正的声明
Troops on the ground is the statement.

399
00:26:28,740 --> 00:26:32,120
不  我想等找到艾哈迈迪再行动
No, I don't want to do anything until we find Ahmadi's location.

400
00:26:32,120 --> 00:26:34,680
我不确定这件事我们应该选择等待  总统女士
I'm not sure we should wait on this, Madam President.

401
00:26:34,930 --> 00:26:37,510
我想提醒你发出最后通牒的
I'd like to remind you that it was this administration

402
00:26:37,510 --> 00:26:39,350
正是这个政府
that introduced the ultimatum.

403
00:26:39,350 --> 00:26:40,720
你该有所行动
You should act on it.

404
00:26:40,720 --> 00:26:42,620
是  但我都没有像样的团队
Yes, but I barely have a team in place.

405
00:26:42,620 --> 00:26:44,270
你可以用前总统的团队
Well, you can run it by the former president...

406
00:26:44,270 --> 00:26:46,120
前总统就是前总统
The former president is just that.

407
00:26:46,120 --> 00:26:47,950
机会就在眼前
An opportunity has presented itself.

408
00:26:47,950 --> 00:26:50,350
而我想把握住机会
And I'm trying to take advantage of it.

409
00:26:51,120 --> 00:26:54,210
-大家都在战况室了吗  -20分钟前都齐了
- Is everyone in the Situation Room? - As of 20 minutes ago.

410
00:27:04,290 --> 00:27:06,610
时机不对
So, the timing is bad.

411
00:27:07,240 --> 00:27:09,790
如果现在赦免他  会显得你跟他的罪行有关
If you pardon him now, you're associated with his crimes.

412
00:27:09,790 --> 00:27:11,620
共和党人会咬着你不放
Republicans will have a field day.

413
00:27:12,220 --> 00:27:13,530
我们需要掩护
We need some cover.

414
00:27:13,970 --> 00:27:15,770
那就是抓捕艾哈迈迪
Well, that would be Ahmadi's capture.

415
00:27:15,770 --> 00:27:17,650
合适的副总统对我们有好处
The right VP would help all this.

416
00:27:17,650 --> 00:27:18,900
你有更多想法吗
Have you had any further thoughts?

417
00:27:18,900 --> 00:27:20,470
最终名单没变
My short list is the same.

418
00:27:20,470 --> 00:27:22,490
韦斯特维尔特  克拉克  克莱因
Westervelt, Clark, Klein.

419
00:27:22,490 --> 00:27:23,850
克莱因最有可能
Klein would be the strongest bulwark

420
00:27:23,850 --> 00:27:25,910
抵抗对你的弹劾
against calls for your impeachment.

421
00:27:26,110 --> 00:27:28,920
-这是剜肉补疮  -补疮是关键
- Swallowing poison to stay alive. - Alive is good.

422
00:27:29,020 --> 00:27:30,210
我觉得我受不了克莱因
I don't think I can stomach Klein.

423
00:27:30,210 --> 00:27:32,390
他称我为贱人  不如克拉克
He called me a bitch. I prefer Clark.

424
00:27:33,150 --> 00:27:35,770
告诉我  搬走尸体前
Tell me. Before you moved the body,

425
00:27:35,770 --> 00:27:38,200
你帮他合上双眼了吗
were you able to close his eyes?

426
00:27:39,090 --> 00:27:40,030
合上了
Yes.

427
00:27:43,120 --> 00:27:47,220
我知道你很重视他的想法
Look... I know his opinion means a lot to you.

428
00:27:48,250 --> 00:27:49,400
弗兰西斯
Francis.

429
00:27:49,700 --> 00:27:52,450
但让他待在白宫  即便在东厢
But having him here, in the White House, even in the East Wing,

430
00:27:52,450 --> 00:27:54,590
也会干扰我们处理事情
while we're trying to figure this out, it's hard.

431
00:27:55,290 --> 00:27:57,040
总会有人暗示
At some point, someone is going to imply

432
00:27:57,040 --> 00:27:59,250
仍是他在做决定
that he is still making the decisions.

433
00:28:00,060 --> 00:28:01,220
那可不妙
That wouldn't be good.

434
00:28:06,900 --> 00:28:09,980
-我会给她建议  她会想通的  -但愿吧
- I'll advise her. She'll come around. - I hope so.

435
00:28:09,980 --> 00:28:13,630
叙利亚的事  如果她现在不行动
Because if she doesn't act now, when it comes to Syria,

436
00:28:13,630 --> 00:28:16,110
她的总统位子就坐不稳
her presidency could be in danger.

437
00:28:16,740 --> 00:28:18,480
你的未来也有变数
And your future in doubt.

438
00:28:18,750 --> 00:28:20,880
别威胁我  戴维斯女士
Oh, don't threaten me, Ms. Davis.

439
00:28:21,260 --> 00:28:22,560
我不威胁别人
I don't threaten.

440
00:28:22,870 --> 00:28:25,520
我只是想尽量说清楚
I just try to remain as clear as possible.

441
00:28:25,520 --> 00:28:29,530
你帮我做事  我也帮你做事
You offered me your services, and I offered you mine.

442
00:28:31,510 --> 00:28:32,560
要知道
You know...

443
00:28:33,760 --> 00:28:36,860
我比你早来  也会比你晚走
I was here before you and I'll be here after you.

444
00:28:37,730 --> 00:28:41,120
即便如此  让我提醒你
And regardless of that, let me remind you...

445
00:28:41,210 --> 00:28:44,930
没有比我更危险的东西
that nothing is more dangerous than me.

446
00:28:47,070 --> 00:28:50,410
你现在得务实  戴维斯没说错
You need to be practical now. Davis isn't wrong.

447
00:28:50,890 --> 00:28:53,850
我们已经想抓捕艾哈迈迪一年了  弗兰西斯
We've been trying to get our hands on Ahmadi for a year, Francis.

448
00:28:53,850 --> 00:28:57,040
-她还没有实现  -没错  但关键不是她
- She hasn't delivered. - Yes, but this isn't about her.

449
00:28:57,040 --> 00:29:00,630
而是你  还有第一次向全国发表讲话
This is about you and coming out with a strong message

450
00:29:00,630 --> 00:29:02,900
传达出来的有力信息
in your first address to the nation.

451
00:29:03,170 --> 00:29:06,950
关键是为你的任期定下基调
This is about setting the course for your presidency.

452
00:29:07,780 --> 00:29:09,670
要强大  克莱尔
Be strong, Claire.

453
00:29:10,310 --> 00:29:12,160
开战吧
Go to war.

454
00:29:18,530 --> 00:29:20,290
但我需要你离开
But I need you to leave.

455
00:29:21,570 --> 00:29:23,050
离开白宫
Leave the White House.

456
00:29:26,190 --> 00:29:27,640
是  我懂
Yes, I see.

457
00:29:33,060 --> 00:29:34,960
为了能成功赦免你  弗兰西斯
For this pardon to succeed, Francis,

458
00:29:34,960 --> 00:29:37,390
我们得表现得有所疏远
we need to appear to be estranged.

459
00:29:39,110 --> 00:29:41,530
这只是策略
I'm just being strategic.

460
00:29:42,340 --> 00:29:44,470
你建议我去哪
And where do you suggest I go?

461
00:29:45,110 --> 00:29:46,490
我不确定
I'm not sure.

462
00:29:48,900 --> 00:29:50,640
海军天文台
The Naval Observatory?

463
00:29:51,330 --> 00:29:53,950
我觉得副总统府邸还是太近了
I think the vice president's residence is still too close.

464
00:29:53,960 --> 00:29:55,450
抱歉  我只是...
I'm sorry, I just...

465
00:29:56,450 --> 00:29:59,150
我们不能让别人认为你还在干政
We can't have anyone think you're still involved in policy.

466
00:29:59,150 --> 00:30:00,540
如果你动摇了
Look, if you're having second thoughts,

467
00:30:00,540 --> 00:30:01,670
-你现在就该告诉我  -不
- you should tell me now. - No.

468
00:30:01,670 --> 00:30:04,010
-我完全同意  -因为这可不是犹豫的时候
- No. I'm in full agreement. - 'Cause this is no time to hesitate.

469
00:30:04,010 --> 00:30:05,610
我没在犹豫
I am not hesitating.

470
00:30:06,350 --> 00:30:08,840
我只是觉得如果我们不妥当处理
I just believe if we don't play this correctly,

471
00:30:08,960 --> 00:30:10,500
那对公众而言
as far as the public,

472
00:30:10,500 --> 00:30:14,440
我的任期不过就是我俩苟且偷生
my term will be nothing but survival for both of us.

473
00:30:15,840 --> 00:30:17,030
好吧
All right.

474
00:30:18,980 --> 00:30:20,600
我希望你知道我会帮助你
I want you to know I'm here

475
00:30:20,600 --> 00:30:28,010
如果你需要政策或其他事情的建议
if you need any advice on policy or anything else you might need.

476
00:30:30,290 --> 00:30:33,080
谢谢你  我去睡了
Thank you. I'm going to bed.

477
00:30:40,530 --> 00:30:43,140
没有人会像我一样爱你
No one will ever love you as much as I do.

478
00:30:44,690 --> 00:30:46,140
我希望你知道
I hope you know that.

479
00:30:47,590 --> 00:30:52,950
就像我知道没有人会像你一样爱我
Just as I know that no one will ever love me... like you.

480
00:32:51,850 --> 00:32:53,680
"在陶瓷青蛙下面"
"Under the porcelain frog."

481
00:32:55,810 --> 00:32:57,850
答案必须准确  包括大小写
The answers are case-sensitive and exact.

482
00:32:57,850 --> 00:32:59,740
只有一次机会
You won't get a second chance.

483
00:33:01,800 --> 00:33:04,840
-第二个问题  -我最喜欢的棒球运动员吗
- And the middle one? - My favorite baseball player?

484
00:33:05,330 --> 00:33:07,550
"韦德·博格斯"  两个G
"Wade Boggs." Two G's.

485
00:33:10,110 --> 00:33:11,670
最后一个
And the last?

486
00:33:11,670 --> 00:33:14,690
"你在奥斯丁的酒店房间留了什么"
"What did you leave in that hotel room in Austin?"

487
00:33:17,350 --> 00:33:18,710
我的枪在哪
Where is my gun?

488
00:33:25,390 --> 00:33:26,550
给
Here you go.

489
00:33:35,360 --> 00:33:36,940
你能给我什么保证
What guarantees do I have?

490
00:33:39,260 --> 00:33:41,050
我把枪还给你了
I gave you your gun back.

491
00:33:44,370 --> 00:33:48,030
但你为什么给他  我很好奇
But what made you give it to him? I'm curious.

492
00:33:49,320 --> 00:33:51,250
我觉得他有危险
I thought he was in danger.

493
00:33:53,660 --> 00:33:55,520
那你现在怎么觉得
And now you think what?

494
00:33:59,250 --> 00:34:01,110
我想问的就是这个
That is what I'm asking.

495
00:34:03,400 --> 00:34:07,970
只要我在  你会一直是本届政府的成员
As long as I'm around, you'll be a part of this administration.

496
00:34:08,610 --> 00:34:10,750
我们都知道艾丹太多事
We both know too much about Aidan.

497
00:34:11,230 --> 00:34:14,620
克莱尔知道你有多忠诚  我很确定
And Claire knows how loyal you are. I'm sure of it.

498
00:34:16,850 --> 00:34:21,570
所以  你在奥斯丁的酒店房间留了什么
So, what did you leave in that hotel room in Austin?

499
00:34:26,240 --> 00:34:27,430
一条手链
A bracelet.

500
00:34:28,710 --> 00:34:30,030
真糟糕
That's too bad.

501
00:34:35,040 --> 00:34:36,500
我终于看到了
You know, I finally got a look

502
00:34:36,500 --> 00:34:39,070
麦卡伦留给哈维小姐的东西
at what Macallan passed on to Ms. Harvey.

503
00:34:39,550 --> 00:34:41,420
你和你丈夫偷走了这场大选
I was shocked to realize the degree

504
00:34:41,420 --> 00:34:43,960
程度之深  真是让我震惊了
to which you and your husband stole this election.

505
00:34:47,540 --> 00:34:48,780
我得对你实话实说
I need to be honest with you.

506
00:34:48,780 --> 00:34:50,660
我和他谈过
I've been in talks with him about

507
00:34:50,700 --> 00:34:53,320
帮他发起一个基金会
helping him start a foundation of some kind.

508
00:34:53,750 --> 00:34:56,120
换取对你的影响
In exchange for influence over you.

509
00:34:59,290 --> 00:35:00,530
有意思
Interesting.

510
00:35:04,810 --> 00:35:07,700
我想帮你度过这个过渡期
I'm trying to help you navigate this transition.

511
00:35:14,980 --> 00:35:16,460
你对于我是什么人
Who are you to me?

512
00:35:18,880 --> 00:35:20,320
你希望我是什么人
Who do you want me to be?

513
00:35:21,100 --> 00:35:22,670
这个回答不好
That's not a good answer.

514
00:35:26,680 --> 00:35:30,770
你是美国第一任女总统
You're the first woman President of the United States.

515
00:35:30,770 --> 00:35:35,100
你忍了那么多  做了那么多牺牲和妥协
All you've had to swallow, the sacrifices, the compromises.

516
00:35:35,100 --> 00:35:37,240
你会想要自我隔离
You're gonna want to isolate yourself.

517
00:35:37,670 --> 00:35:39,280
不去相信任何人
Not trust anyone.

518
00:35:39,390 --> 00:35:41,740
但你需要的正是这个
But that's exactly what you're gonna need.

519
00:35:41,750 --> 00:35:44,080
需要有人告诉你真相
Someone to tell you what's what.

520
00:35:45,370 --> 00:35:47,070
你就是这个人吗
And is that person you?

521
00:35:51,730 --> 00:35:52,900
是吗
Is it?

522
00:35:53,270 --> 00:35:56,160
我觉得不论我说什么都没法让你相信
I don't think there's anything i could say that would convince you

523
